EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 212300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A TROUGH LYING E-W ACROSS CENTRAL WATERS OF PORTPATRICK
WILL PROBABLY DRIFT SWARDS DURING FRIDAY AS PRESSURE BUILDS IN ITS WAKE.
BY THE END OF THE DAY A BROAD RIDGE IS FCST TO LIE FM ICELAND TO DENMARK
WITH THE TROUGH LYING ACROSS FAR SERN WATERS. ON SATURDAY THE RIDGE REMAINS
SLOW-MOV WITH A DPN LOW OVER FITZROY 988 TO START THE DAY BEFORE TRACKING
TO FRANCE. CONFIDENCE VERY LOW FOR DETAIL BY THIS TIME WITH THE LOW PROBABLY
FLN AS A SLOW-MOV FEATURE. ANOTHER LOW MAY DEVELOP SHANNON 987 BY MIDDAY.
DURING THURSDAY NIGHT GALES OR SEV GALES AFFECTING MOST NERN WATERS WILL
CONTINUE INTO FRIDAY WITH WINDS DECR ACROSS FAIR ISLE FAEROES AND S E ICELAND.
ON SATURDAY GALES PERHAPS SEV CONTINUING S OF 59 N WITH WINDS GENERALLY
DECR ACROSS THIS AREA BY SUNDAY BUT CONFIDENCE IN DETAIL BECOMES VERY LOW
